<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id74a8715a-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s154709"><num value="154709">§ 154709.</num><heading> Duty to maintain tax-exempt status</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The corporation shall maintain its status as an organization exempt from taxation under the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 (<ref href="/us/usc/t26/s1">26 U.S.C. 1</ref> et seq.).</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id74a8715b-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1438">112 Stat. 1438</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
